  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We show that every locally finite bipartite Borel graph satisfying a strengthening of Hall's condition has a Borel perfect matching on some comeager invariant Borel set. We apply this to show that if a group acting by Borel automorphisms on a Polish space has a paradoxical decomposition, then it admits a paradoxical decomposition using pieces having the Baire property. This strengthens a theorem of Dougherty and Foreman who showed that there is a paradoxical decomposition of the unit ball in <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="double-struck">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math> using Baire measurable pieces. We also obtain a Baire category solution to the dynamical von Neumann–Day problem: if a is a nonamenable action of a group on a Polish space X by Borel automorphisms, then there is a free Baire measurable action of <math altimg="si13.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="double-struck">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math> on X which is Lipschitz with respect to a .</subfield>
